  "body": "With the first desktop beta release coming up we would like to make the releases available on https://github.com/status-im/status-react/releases. This is convenient, findable, and a convention for many projects.\r\n\r\nCurrently there are over 4300 releases. These have no context and are automated for every build and tag.\r\n\r\nLet's prep these things:\r\n\r\n- Stop these automated releases\r\n- Clear out all 4k+\r\n- New release can be manual now\r\n- [future] Eventually we can use the Github Release API and integrate with our Jenkins workflow. \n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/11767950?s=400&v=4\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/favicon.ico\" height=\"14\"> GitHub</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-react\">status-im/status-react</a></strong></div><div>a free (libre) open source, mobile OS for Ethereum - status-im/status-react</div></blockquote>",
